# Refactoring Rules

## Before Refactoring

1. Ensure all tests pass (`npm test`)
2. Check `docs/audits/CODE_AUDIT.md` for known smells
3. Check `docs/roadmaps/TECH_DEBT_ROADMAP.md` for priority

## Principles

- Minimal, focused diffs
- One concern per PR
- No drive-by cleanup of unrelated code
- Match existing code style in each file
- Remove imports made unused by YOUR changes only

## Safe Refactors

- Extract geocode helper from campground controller
- Remove unused imports and dead commented code
- Add database indexes to models
- Rename `isloggedIn` → `isLoggedIn` (update all references)

## Risky Refactors (Require Tests First)

- Moving Cloudinary cleanup out of model hook
- Introducing service layer
- Changing session configuration
- Modifying cascade delete behavior

## After Refactoring

Run `npm test` and verify no behavior change unless intended.
